         <critic>Desson Thomson</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>Formulaic but innocuous little movie's one clever moment, a sing-off between choirs standing on their respective church steps, trying to lure in Sunday-morning worshippers.</snippet>
         <url>http://www.laweekly.com/film+tv/film-reviews/film-reviews/13131/</url>
         <critic>Chuck Wilson</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>Call this one "Brother Act." Instead of Whoopi Goldberg's Reno lounge singer in "Sister Act,"  Preaching to the Choir has a hip-hop star hiding out from a gangsta record producer in his estranged brother-minister's Harlem church.</snippet>
         <url>http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr/reviews/review_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1002343505</url>
